The paper deals with video style transfer, which involves computer vision and image processing techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces an adversarial learning framework, which falls under the category of generative models and machine learning, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses non-photorealistic rendering, which falls under the category of computer graphics, making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
